<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black;">Unlike commercial loans, personal loans are made simply to finance a purchase or transaction, not as an investment to finance a particular piece of equipment or office space. &nbsp;While the reasons for seeking personal loans naturally vary, there are features and considerations that are common to nearly all personal loans. Becoming educated about how personal loans work can help borrowers obtain the best possible terms.</span></p>
<h2 class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black;">Types of Personal Loans</span></strong></h2>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black;">When it comes to personal loans, borrowers are spoiled for choice. There are nearly as many types of personal loans as there are reasons to borrow. One of the things that set lenders apart is the types of loans that they offer.</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Secured Loans:</span></u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> Secured loans are guaranteed by collateral. Many secured loans are guaranteed through a lien on property purchased with the loan. Other secured loans are secured by personal property that is owned by the borrower, such as jewelry.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Unsecured Loans:</span></u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> Unsecured loans are also known as signature loans, because they are guaranteed only by signed agreements by borrowers to repay. In general, unsecured loans require borrowers to present excellent credit, a creditworthy co-signer, or both.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Peer-to-Peer Loans:</span></u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> In recent years, online peer-to-peer personal loans have emerged as alternatives to conventional personal loans. Peer-to-peer personal loans adapt the crowd funding model to provide personal loans. Peer-to-peer lenders often require extensive personal information in addition to financial and income information that is included in conventional personal loans. Peer-to-peer personal loans can also require lengthy waits, and there are no guarantees that loan applications will be funded.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Payday Loans:</span></u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> &nbsp;Short term loans that carry high interest rates and relatively small dollar amounts. They are usually structured to require a single payment rather than installments. Payday loans are issued by payday loan stores or by online payday lenders.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Installment Loans:</span></u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> Long-term loans that carry lower interest rates and higher dollar amounts than payday loans. Repayment is structured in monthly installments. Installment loans are issued by banks, credit unions and nonbank lenders.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2 class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black;">Loan Amount Options</span></strong></h2>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black;">Many installment lenders require a relatively high loan amount (1,000 or more), while some payday lenders will provide loans as low as 50 dollars! &nbsp;Such small loans dont make money for payday lenders  their profits are mainly obtained by administrative fees and compounded interest rates charged on rollovers (described below). After only a few rollovers, small loans often mushroom into major financial obligations, and borrowers often find themselves owing more than they originally borrowed, even after making regular payments for months!</span></p>
<h2 class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black;">Fees and Interest</span></strong></h2>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black;">Just as there are many types of loans, there are numerous fees and interest charges associated with borrowing money. The list below includes some of the most common forms of fees and interest charges associated with personal loans.</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Origination Fees</span></u><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">: </span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;Fees imposed when loans are issued. Such fees are usually subtracted from the loan amount, so that borrowers receive less than they actually borrowed.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Early Termination Fees</span></u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">: These fees impose a financial penalty on borrowers who pay off their loans before the repayment period has concluded. They allow lenders to recover the potential profit loss from interest payments they dont receive when borrowers pay off their loans early.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Re-Issue or Renewal Fees</span></u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">: &nbsp;Also known as rollovers, these fees occur when borrowers are unable to repay their loans in full. &nbsp;In these circumstances, borrowers submit a partial payment and lenders refinance the remainder in a new loan.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Higher Interest Loans:</span></u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> Borrowers with poor credit and no collateral are often forced to borrow loans at much higher interest rates than borrowers with good credit. These loans also frequently include other undesirable features such as early termination fees.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Low Interest Loans</span></u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">: Borrowers with good or excellent credit often find lenders are eager to do business with them, and receive loan offers with desirable incentives such as travel related awards, along with low interest rates</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Fixed Rate Loans</span></u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">: &nbsp;Interest rates remain constant throughout the life of the loan. Fixed rates loans offer predictability, and are desirable when interest rates are low.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Variable Rate Loans: </span></u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Loans with interest rates that vary according to market conditions. Variable rate loans often have low initial interest rates, and can be attractive if they are paid off before interest rates rise.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Lines of Credit</span></u><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">: Lines of credit represent a form of revolving credit. The amount of credit decreases with withdrawals, and is replenished when payments are made.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2 class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black;">Lending Sources for Personal Loans</span></strong></h2>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black;">Applications for personal loans from conventional sources require underwriting to determine the creditworthiness of borrowers. &nbsp;Borrowers must submit credit and income information and, in some cases, the specific purpose of the loan. The processing of personal loans from conventional sources can be lengthy. There are several potential lending sources for personal loans some good  some, like payday lenders -- should be avoided at all costs.</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Banks and Credit Unions</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Finance Companies</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Peer-to-Peer Lenders (e.g. Prosper)</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Lending Brokers (e.g. &nbsp;Lending Tree)</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Borrower-specific Lenders (e.g. military loans)</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Payday Lenders</span></li>
</ul>
<h2 class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black;">Is a Personal Loan Right for You?</span></strong></h2>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black;">If you find yourself facing one of the following types of circumstances, or something similar, a personal loan may be a good solution for you.</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Emergency auto or home repair</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Unexpected medical or other bills</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Refinancing high interest (e.g. credit card) debt</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list .5in; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Starting or expanding a small business</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black;">On the other hand, if youre looking for a personal loan to cover day-to-day expenses, you may be better off seeking financial counseling instead. In extreme circumstances, bankruptcy may be your best option to give yourself a fresh start. However, you should definitely consult with a professional before taking such a drastic step, however.</span></p><div class="sm-clear"></div>
